DPM_TEAM04.navigation

Class Search

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Thread
      • DPM_TEAM04.navigation.Search
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable

    public class Search
extends java.lang.Thread
    Once the localization is done, the search thread is started. It starts searching optimally and drives to the first object it sees. It then analyses if it is a styrofoam block or an obstacle. It picks the styrofoam blocks and brings it back to its zone. Otherwise it goes back to its searching point and keep searching for styrofoam blocks.
    Author:
    Alexis Giguere-Joannette, Tristan Toupin

      • search

        public static void search()
        Performs the search. Scans with the front ultrasonic sensor until it gets close enough to a block. Once it is close to a block it calls scanBlock() to analyse the block.

      • isObjectSeen

        public static boolean isObjectSeen(double USDistance)
        Interprets the data from the front ultrasonic sensor to determine if there is an object seen or if it is a wall.
        Parameters:
        USDistance - Data from the ultrasonic sensor.
        Returns:
        Returns true if there is an object seen. Returns false if no object is seen.

      • scanning

        public static void scanning()
        Turn the robot either clockwise or counter-clockwise to search the area.

      • scanBlock

      • notBlock

        public static void notBlock()
        If it is not a block, go back to the search point and continue searching.

      • wallSeen

        public static void wallSeen()
        If the object is too close to a wall (or inside the green or red zone), turn instantly in the direction it was scanning.

      • captureBlock

        public static void captureBlock()
        If the object scanned is a styrofoam block, grab the block, travel back to the waypoints and to the stack point, drop the block according to the @towerHeight and return back to the search points (passing by the waypoints to avoid obstacles).
